							<div class="post_wrapper author">
								<div id="about_the_author">
									<div class="gravatar"><a href="https://lithub.com/author/mollyrodenwinter/"><img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Screen-Shot-2024-01-09-at-10.45.34-AM-100x100.png" width="100" height="100" alt="Molly Roden Winter" class="avatar avatar-100 wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-100 alignnone photo" /></a></div>
									<div class="description author withsidebar">
										<h6><a href="https://lithub.com/author/mollyrodenwinter/">Molly Roden Winter</a></h6>
										Molly Roden Winter was raised in Evanston, Illinois, and lives in Park Slope, Brooklyn, with her husband and two sons. Her personal essays have appeared in <em>Motherwell</em>, <em>Pangyrus</em>, and <em>Capsule Stories</em>. She is half of the guitar-playing, song-writing duo House of Mirth.																				<div class="website">
			    							<i class="fa fa-link"></i>
				    						<a href="http://www.mollyrodenwinter.com" target="_blank" class="external">http://www.mollyrodenwinter.com</a>
